Centrally positioned within close proximity to Portumna, Birr, and Lorrha Village, viewing is available strictly by appointment. sale_ad.description:
One of Tipperarys Finest Homes

This beautifully constructed Six-bedroom, three-storey home over 4,000 sqft 

offers commanding views of Lough Derg and surrounded by rolling countryside, this exceptional five-bedroom, three-storey residence is a masterpiece of craftsmanship and design.

On the ground floor, a bright and expansive open-plan kitchen, living, and dining area invites you in, seamlessly connecting to a sun-soaked outdoor patioideal for alfresco dining or simply soaking in the panoramic views. This level also includes a generously proportioned utility room and a convenient WC with shower.

The bespoke oak kitchen is both stylish and functional, featuring a mix of granite and hardwood countertops, along with an inset Rangemaster cookerperfect for family meals or entertaining guests. The adjoining living area boasts a striking stone fireplace with an inset stove, creating a warm and inviting atmosphere.

A stunning handcrafted oak staircase leads to the first floor, where you'll find four beautifully appointed bedrooms, a spacious secondary living room, and a dedicated office space. The living room is a standout feature, complete with a charming keystone fireplace and a glass-enclosed seating area that frames uninterrupted views of the lake and countryside.

The master bedroom offers a touch of luxury with its private en-suite, walk-in wardrobe, and a personal verandaan idyllic spot to enjoy your morning coffee while taking in the tranquil landscape.

The top floor adds even more versatility, with a second kitchen and two additional bed rooms that can serve as guest accommodation, independent living quarters, or a family entertainment suite.

Built to the highest standards, this home showcases exquisite stonework, a natural slate roof, and sits on a secluded one-acre site with a large garage for additional storage or workshop potential.
Garrykennedy lakeside village is within a short driving distance and 10 km from Nenagh town and the m7 motorway. 

Viewing is strictly by appointment only through the selling agents, BOC Properties. Dont miss the opportunity to own this remarkable home in one of Tipperarys most sought-after locations.

A Stunning Turn-Key Property in a Prime Location
This beautifully presented B3 energy-rated home extends to approximately 3,000 sq. ft. and includes a separate garage. Built and finished to the highest standards, this exceptional residence combines modern luxury with elegant design and enjoys fantastic hill views.
Inside, the home features a bespoke walnut staircase and walnut flooring throughout much of the property. Currently configured as a three-bedroom home, it could easily be adapted to a five bedroom layout with minor modifications to the loft area (subject to planning permission).
The spacious kitchen and living area boasts vaulted ceilings, custom built kitchen units, a large island, and marble worktops, creating a perfect space for both family living and entertaining.
All bedrooms are generously sized, with the master bedroom offering a large en-suite bathroom and a walk-in wardrobe. The sitting room features built-in units, a wood-burning stove, and walnut hardwood flooring, adding to the warmth and charm of the home.
The master bathroom has that wow factor to it where you can clearly see the influences of the interior designer. 
Outside, the extensive landscaped lawns are beautifully maintained and make a striking impression on approach to the property. The stylish exterior design showcases quality stonework and discreet lighting under the soffits, enhancing its appeal at night.
Located on a quiet secondary road, the property enjoys a peaceful setting while remaining close to the lakeside village of Garrykennedy, Nenagh town, and the M7 motorway, approximately 12 km away.
Offers in access of 495,000
